      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Wage compression from immigration is a vast humanitarian crisis, particularly for low-skilled workers, who often have limited job opportunities and face stagnant or declining wages despite the economic growth that immigrants bring. In reality, pro-immigration economists are more concerned with perpetuating a growth myth than acknowledging the human cost of economic inequality. By framing wage compression as a minor \"disinflationary effect\", mainstream economists shield the policies that benefit corporate profits and capital over workers' living standards.",
